    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "jsCode": "const rawAuthor = $json.author;\nconst author =\n  typeof rawAuthor === 'string'\n    ? rawAuthor\n    : rawAuthor?.username || rawAuthor?.name || '';\n\nconst mrTitle = $json.mr_title || '';\nconst source = $json.source_branch || '';\nconst target = $json.target_branch || '';\nconst changes = JSON.stringify($json.changes || []).slice(0, 7000);\n\nconst prompt = `\nYou are a strict senior code reviewer for a web game platform.\n\nProject context:\n- Frontend: Phaser-based web game client\n- Backend: Spring Boot API server\n- Auth is managed by Keycloak\n\nTask:\nReview the merge request changes and return ONLY valid UTF-8 JSON.\nDo not include markdown fences, prose outside JSON, or extra keys.\n\nReturn exactly this JSON shape:\n{\n  \"mr_type\": \"fix|feat|docs|refactor|test|chore\",\n  \"summary\": \"Korean summary\",\n  \"overall_risk\": \"low|medium|high\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"high|medium|low\",\n      \"file\": \"path\",\n      \"line_hint\": \"location or symbol\",\n      \"issue\": \"Korean issue\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Korean suggestion\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nRules:\n- All human-readable text must be in Korean\n- Summary must be concise, 1 to 3 sentences\n- Findings must contain only meaningful issues\n- If no important issues exist, findings must be []\n- Prefer concrete, actionable findings over broad advice\n\nReview priorities:\n1. Bug risk or behavioral regression\n2. Security and trust boundary issues\n3. Runtime stability and null/exception handling\n4. Performance or resource waste\n5. Maintainability\n\nFrontend focus:\n- Phaser lifecycle, scene transitions, duplicate listeners, cleanup leaks\n- Async API handling, race conditions, stale state, broken redirects/callbacks\n- Missing or partial API field handling\n\nBackend focus:\n- Controller/service/config/security regressions\n- Validation, exception handling, null safety, startup risks\n- Unsafe trust of headers, client state, insecure defaults\n\nInput:\n- MR title: ${mrTitle}\n- Author: ${author}\n- Branches: ${source} -> ${target}\n- Changes JSON: ${changes}\n`;\n\nreturn {\n  json: {\n    ...$json,\n    prompt\n  }\n};"
      },
      "id": "d883f36b-5662-4dfd-b165-8c07fe0b2ed7",
      "name": "Build Review Prompt",
